

# GrowMaster + MacPlants Import Review

## Executive Summary

Data import from GrowMaster and MacPlants is now operational end-to-end:

- Plants imported with deduplicated size business keys.
- Customers imported including rows without email.
- Vouchers imported.
- Orders imported with historical line-item price snapshots and delivery costs.
- Orders analytics tab added under Orders with league tables and revenue trend chart.

## What Worked Well

- Import scripts are now deterministic and repeatable with truncate + reload workflow.
- Large datasets were processed in batches successfully.
- Legacy GM key migration strategy worked without forcing a risky primary key rewrite.
- Order import now supports nullable customer match fallback (email first, then name).
- Analytics can be filtered by:

- Time window (1 to 5 years)

- Customer type (all, retail, trade)

- Plant

- Dashboard outputs now cover:

- Best/worst plants

- Best/worst customers

- Best customers and preferred plants

- Revenue line graph over time

